<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="469" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1620,2035]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1797,1822]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">Remarks.</emphasis>
The tail valve (
<figureCitation box="[506,592,1797,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="19.[151,249,917,939]" captionTargetBox="[163,1409,195,886]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,173,917]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 16. Leptoplax richardi, Southern Vietnam, Cau Id.: A. Valve VIII, dorsal view; B. Valve VIII, lateral view; C. Valve VIII, detail of tegmentum in antemucronal area." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837003/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) which is the only known specimen of this species collected during the survey of collected sand is identifiable to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaas, 1990" authorityName="Kaas" authorityYear="1990" box="[643,987,1832,1857]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Acanthochitonidae" genus="Notoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="richardi">
<emphasis box="[643,847,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">Notoplax richardi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas" box="[857,987,1833,1857]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" refString="Kaas, P. (1990) New species and further records of known species of Polyplacophora from the tropical western Pacific. Basteria, 54, 175 - 186." type="journal article" year="1990">Kaas, 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaas, 1990" authorityName="Sirenko &amp; Saito" authorityYear="2017" box="[1033,1405,1832,1857]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Acanthochitonidae" genus="Leptoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="richardi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[1033,1246,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">Leptoplax richardi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas" box="[1264,1396,1833,1857]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" refString="Kaas, P. (1990) New species and further records of known species of Polyplacophora from the tropical western Pacific. Basteria, 54, 175 - 186." type="journal article" year="1990">Kaas, 1990</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="18" pageNumber="469">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
] described from Coral Sea, at the depth of 
<quantity box="[717,776,1868,1893]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" unit="m" value="56.0">56 m</quantity>
by the outline of tegmentum, wavy margins of the jugum which has oblique sulci and 2–7 micraesthete pores distributed in the proximal half of the pustule.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1620,2035]" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">
The generic assignment of this species is changed from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Adams" authorityYear="1861" box="[829,932,1939,1964]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Acanthochitonidae" genus="Notoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[829,932,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">Notoplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1882" box="[968,1080,1939,1964]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Acanthochitonidae" genus="Leptoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[968,1080,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">Leptoplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herein, based on the diagnostic features of the sutural laminae of the tail valve and the central part of the radula. The latter is shown in 
<bibRefCitation author="Saito" pageId="18" pageNumber="469" refString="Saito, H. (1998) The chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) of the Goto Islands, west coast of Kyushu, Japan. Memoir of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, 31, 145 - 163." type="journal article" year="1998">
Saito (1998: 159, 
<figureCitation box="[207,272,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1700,1722]" captionTargetBox="[277,1283,203,1612]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[257,1330,173,1750]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Notoplax odysseyi n. sp., Southern Vietnam, Off Phan Rang, holotype, BL 51 mm: A. Needle of tufts; B. Dorsal needles, C. Ventral spicules, D. Head of major lateral tooth of radula; E. Central and first lateral teeth of radula; F. Pustule of lateropleural areas of tegmentum. Scale bars: 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/836987/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="469">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
A)
</bibRefCitation>
. This is the first record of this species from Vietnamese waters.
</paragraph>
